        "TRL": "9",
        "Keywords": "",
        "Description": "A catalytic methanation (Sabatier) reactor model operating at 30 bar using the TREMP multi-stage process, converting compressed CO2 and green hydrogen into synthetic natural gas (CH4) and water. The model includes three inter-stage cooling hot streams (stages at 542→300°C, 411→200°C, 202→40°C), a CO2 compressor utility (1 to 30 bar, 3-stage), and annualized investment costs for both reactor and compression.",
        "DOI": "",
        "Main Related Publication": "",
        "References": "(1) https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fenrg.2018.00005; (2) Florez-Orrego et al. Journal of Cleaner Production 244 (2020) 118647",
        "Software": "",
        "Software File": "",
        "Block Flow Diagram": "",
        "URL": "",
        "Supplementary Material": "See SUPPL MATERIAL tab"
